Commercial CPUE index standardization (Tweedie version)

Source: R/cpue-index-tweedie.R
cpue-tweedie.Rd

  • tidy_cpue_index_coefs_tweedie() extracts coefficients from a CPUE index standardization model

fit_cpue_index_tweedie(dat, formula = cpue ~ year_factor)

predict_cpue_index_tweedie(object, center = FALSE)

tidy_cpue_index_coefs_tweedie(object, include_scale_pars = FALSE,
  re_name = c("RE 1", "RE 2"))

Arguments

dat

A data frame to fit. Might be from tidy_cpue_index() or tidy_cpue_historic().
formula

Formula A formula with up to 2 random intercepts in lme4 syntax. Must contain a predictor named year_factor that contains the year as a factor.
object

Output from fit_cpue_index_tweedie().
center

Should the predictions be centered by dividing by the geometric mean?
include_scale_pars

Logical: include observation CV and random effect like standard deviations in parameter plot?
re_name

Names for the possible random intercepts. Should start with RE.

Examples

set.seed(1)
d <- sim_cpue()
# assign factor levels with base as most common level:
d$vessel <- gfplot::f(d$vessel)
m1 <- fit_cpue_index_tweedie(d, cpue ~ year_factor + vessel)
